<br>
Same thing with this guy.  I mean one EQ player, out of what 450K+ subscribers, commits suicide and its because he played EQ.  Nothing to do with the fact that he was diagnosed with Schizophenia, lived alone, and had little if any social contact outside playing EQ.  I wonder how he paid for his appartment and the month EQ bill, if he wasnt working.<br>
<br>
Its not just families looking for someone/something to place blame on.  A lot of it has to do with how the media chooses to portray RPGs and RPG players.  While most stories dont outright claim RPGs cause these problems,  they use language that implies a causal relationship, that has no factual evidence.  Lord, I hate the media!!<br>
<br>
Guess Im not playing enough EQ.  I can actually think logically.<br>
<br>
/step of soapbox<br>
<br>
Rant is over. Now back to playing EQ and  not writing my term papers.<br>
