<br>
Who knows, EQ might have ruined him in some way we don't get from the story, we've all seen people who's marriages were ruined by Everquest and we all know addicts of Everquest, this guy is just another in that category who took his own like instead of seeking help.<br>
<br>
I don't believe the mother should sue, or should even have considered it.  In a suicide like this, the first to be blamed should be those close to the person, and in this case, it would be the parents or the mother.  They did not bring it up with their son and now she needs a scapegoat to cover her own inadequacy (sic?) as a parent.<br>
<br>
It's a sad incident, but Everquest, like everything else that is addictive, can lead some over the edge.  The only difference with Everquest is you can stop, it doesn't cause a chemical imbalance that makes your body crave it more and more unless it's some sort of crazy psychopatic experience, by which I mean the person is a schizophrene (sic?), otherwise, nothing about EQ should be able to cause an addiction so bad you have to kill yourself to escape it.<br>
<br>
